question: 栃木県
sourceMnemonic: The <kanji>prefecture</kanji> with lots of <kanji>horse chestnut</kanji> <kanji>tree</kanji>s is <vocabulary>Tochigi prefecture</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This word consists of the kun'yomi readings for <ja>栃</ja> and <ja>木</ja> and the on'yomi for <ja>県</ja>, like most with prefectures. As long as you remember that <ja>き</ja> is changed to <ja>ぎ</ja> here, you should be able to remember this reading easily!
